interactions.flavorLineOne: You recovered the methane reactor and helped prevent further power shortages.  All systems are fully functional.  Sloane thanks you.

Sloane takes the recovered tech and listens to your report. "Savathûn," she repeats. "So it's worse than I thought."

"I was able to do a little research on this tech. Pieces of survival gear from the Golden Age—and they're just my size. When that ship decides to land, I'll be here to deal with whatever walks out of it."

The resolute look in Sloane's eyes stops you from speaking.

"When it all started, me, Zavala, Shaxx… we didn't build the wall; we were the wall." The unbreakable woman's voice is unexpectedly soft. "I told Zavala once: I was there for the beginning, and I'll be there for the end."

She smiles. Her crow's feet crinkle.

"It's not the end yet."

"A welcome face. Thanks for all you've done for us. The fragile existence we're holding onto is maintained only through the efforts of Guardians like yourself."

interactions.flavorLineOne: Even if the Vanguard doesn't support you, Sloane does. She understands what it's like to lose a comrade. Sometimes, a Guardian has to follow their heart. No matter where it leads you.

headerDisplayProperties.description: When a Guardian dies, the entire community mourns them. Go check in on Sloane to see how she's doing.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Sloane

interactions.flavorLineOne: Sloane, always up for a challenge, looks eager to test the durability of the nigh-unbreakable cookies.
Sloane's stern demeanor doesn't crack when you hand her the gift, but she's never been one for effusive displays of gratitude.

Sloane thanks you for the work you've done in securing Titan.

New challenges appear on the horizon, however.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Sloane is impressed with your many successful adventures on Titan. Speak with her in the Command Center.

interactions.flavorLineOne:
With your help, Sloane secured our hold on Titan. Unfortunately, ongoing enemy activity remains a threat. There are reports of Fallen threatening this rig's stability on the ocean surface. 

Clear the Fallen threat.

The control center is secure and operational. Now it's time to focus on those intercepted Red Legion transmissions, which could provide a significant advantage in the war. Amanda Holliday needs the power of the central processing units in the bowels of the Arcology to crack the encryption. 

Retrieve a Golden Age CPU by completing mission "Utopia."

"You're back," Sloane says. "I've been sending supplies to Zavala, but I'm not finished here. Not yet."

"The Hive's preparing a massive ritual beneath the Arcology. Get in there and stop them. They want us to back off, which means we push harder."

"There's also activity on the surface. Some kind of Hive Treasurer has been dredging up Golden Age tech… and I've been letting it." She raises a hand to quiet your protests. "They've been looking for something specific. And they finally found it."

"You just have to go pick it up."

The data you recovered from the Fallen indicate there is a functional methane reactor somewhere on the abandoned rig. If you can recover it, Sloane will be able to prevent additional power shortages. 

Find the Methane Reactor and bring it back online.

"I was wondering who Zavala would send," Sloane says as you arrive. She seems pleased to see you. "He's watching the skies, but I'm more concerned about what's happening on the ground."

"I'm seeing increased hostile activity across the board. The Hive's digging deep for Golden Age tech. They know the Pyramids have us distracted, and they're taking everything they can reach."

In the distance, you hear the unearthly cackling of Hive. "They think they can pick our bones before we're dead?"

She squares her shoulders. The medals on her spaulders clink softly. "Not a chance."

"Good work out there," Sloane tells you.

"I'll put together a plan. In the meantime, you just keep sending those Hive back through their portals in little pieces."

She falls silent, lost for a moment in the shadow of the Pyramid. She looks out over Titan's tumultuous seas, her jaw set, her mouth a hard line.

You nod. Sloane nods back. It's enough.

With your help, Sloane secured our hold on Titan. Unfortunately, ongoing enemy activity remains a threat. There are reports of Fallen threatening this rig's stability on the ocean surface. 

Clear the Fallen threat.

"Welcome to Titan, Guardian. The situation here is stable, but… The Rig. The Sinking Docks. The Solarium. Every inch of this old structure's under constant threat from the Hive and Fallen."

Sloane offers bounties, quests, and more to Guardians who help her defend Titan.
